fey: ...Anyways, that's the situation.
fey: I'm out of money.
fey: You two are going to need to find a job.
It was quite the predicament I had found myself in, on that rainy afternoon.
My sister and I were lazing around at home. I was perusing the contents of a magazine and Kyuki reclined herself halfway across a bean bag couch. She was as asleep as she could possibly be, vacantly staring at the logs that made up the ceiling of our home.
It was then that our aunt walked in, and said that word.
"Job."
Yes, that one. I couldn't believe my ears.
kyuki: ...
Before I knew it, blood had started to leak out of my sister's mouth. And quite a lot of it at that.
fey: What the hell?!
kei: Auntie. Please. Don't say such things in front of sister dearest. You know how she gets around that word.
kyuki: I'm fine. Don't worry about me.
fey: You started throwing up blood! There's no way you're fine!
kyuki: It's alright, Auntie. We understand what you're trying to say.
kyuki: Indeed.
fey: What?
kyuki: You don't love me anymore, right? You're abandoning me.
kyuki: It makes sense. I spend every waking second in my room, eating chips, drinking cola.
kyuki: I'm ugly. I smell bad. I don't shower. Even worse, I ate your pudding from the fridge yesterday without asking.
kyuki: I might as well die.
kei: Oh, I see. I wait tables at the cafe from time to time, so I can stay, right?
fey: What are you talking about? Stop joking around. I'm serious.
fey: I'm broke. We're completely out of money.
fey: Truth be told, with how poor business has been in the past few months and the fact that I've had three mouths to feed, I'm shocked my savings even lasted this long.
fey: But last night, the final due date for those loans I took out for the remodeling finally came.
fey: I managed to convince our debtor to forgive a quarter of the loan but the remainder of the loan drained our savings completely.
fey: I'm out of money.
kyuki: N-no way... Are we going to have to move back with mom? After all that bragging you did?
fey: It's fine! As long as you two manage to bring in some money starting now, we'll stay afloat.
kei: ...Hey, hang on. That story doesn't add up. We made enough revenue last quarter to pay off at least 4/5ths of the balance.
kei: Where's the rest?
fey: H-huh?
kei: I did the accounting myself. Our seasonal revenue was 16,495 gold. We loaned a principal of 10,000 gold at a 5% rate, which would've racked up 122 gold in interest over the course of the last three months.
kei: Our business expenditures this quarter totaled only 6438 gold. The three of us haven't made a single purchase in the past three months outside of food and other necessities.
kei: Where's the rest of the money?
fey: ...
kei: You gambled it away, didn't you?
fey: ...
fey: ...Tch.
She looked away from us.
fey: What does that matter to you?! It's my money! I can do whatever I want with it!
kyuki: Wow. Instantly busted.
kei: We were doing fine last week, weren't we? How did you even manage to lose a grand in a week?
kyuki: Wait, we made seventeen thousand gold this year?
kyuki: How? Doesn't Auntie sell like six cakes a day?
kyuki: To be honest, I thought we were drowning in debt... I was readying myself to sell one of Kei's kidney's soon...
kei: Half of it came from mom.
kyuki: Oh. Makes sense.
kyuki: So you were blowing away our child support money on Mahjong, huh?
fey: Shut up! That's not true! And it's not like it's your money anyways! You two haven't done anything!
fey: All you do is laze around! And sleep! And read magazines!
fey: You two need to clean up after yourselves! What are you going to do when I die, huh?!
fey: Who's going to cook for you?! Who's going to wash your clothes?! Who's going to pay the rent?!
fey: You two need to get a job! Now!!!
kei: Hang on, you can't expect us to just instantly get a job. We don't have any qualifications or marketable skills.
kei: Even adventuring requires a license from the Guild which would take at least a week to process.
fey: That won't be a problem. I've already registered the two of you.
kei: Huh? When?
fey: Ages ago. Also, you're both my collateral for the rest of the debt. I made a deal with the guy that you'd mentor his daughter next week and I told him you two reached the sixth floor on your own.
kei: You registered us without telling us? And wait...
kei: The sixth floor?! You insane hag, do you know how hard that is?!  It's not even legal for F-Rankers to enter the sixth floor! Solo delvers are supposed to have years of experience!
kei: And you lied to the Dragons? Do you want to get us killed?! What if they find out?!
fey: Blah blah, I don't want to hear it. You're smart, you'll figure it out. And Kei's a Doll, so she's already at an advantage.
kei: That doesn't solve anything!
fey: You'll be fine. Here, I even bought you a sword to celebrate the occasion.
fey: Don't come back home until you're level 2!
leave fey
