kei: ...This game doesn't even have levels!
kyuki: She really kicked us out. Maybe she does hate us.
She threw us out on to the street and closed the door behind us. Auntie must've been feeling extra generous, because she also handed us a duffel bag with enough rations for a few days and a little bit of pocket money.
kyuki: Well, it was a good run. I'm gonna go back to Vermillion and live with mom.
kei: Hold it.
I grabbed her by the cuff as she started to walk away.
kei: You wouldn't be able to find her if you tried. There's no guarantee she's even in Vermillion anymore.
kyuki: Can't I just go back to our old house and live there, then?
kei: That place was raided by the VDA years ago. Forget living there, you'd be arrested on sight for even entering the premises.
kyuki: ...
kyuki: Ha...
kyuki: So it's come down to this...
kyuki: We're done for, Kei. Let's just get this over with and kill ourselves.
kei: You're overexaggerating. Let's just go to the guild and collect our licenses.
