tina: ...And so, the two of you will have to start as F-Ranks. Your registration has been pre-approved, so if you want, you can start immediately.
tina: I would advise at least reading over the manual beforehand though. It's not common, but beginners do sometimes recieve permanent injuries or even die on the fifth floor.
kei: What are the requirements for us to travel to the sixth?
tina: You'll need to be an E-Rank adventurer at the minimum accompanying a D-Rank or above. Only D-Ranks and above are qualified to venture down to the sixth floor alone.
tina: Do you have an item you need from the floor? I can submit a retrieval request for you if you'd like.
kei: No thanks.
tina: It's telling me that you two don't belong to a Company yet. Would you like me to register a Company for you?
kei: Please, if possible.
tina: Do have a name in mind?
kei: Fey's Ca-
kyuki: Kyuki and Friends! Kyuki and Friends! Kyuki and Friends!
tina: Kyuki and Friends. You will be registered under the Open Forest. If you would like to transfer Unions, you can carry over any Company records and ranking progress.
tina: Please call for me the next time you visit this branch of the Guild. I would suggest doing a joint expedition with a more experienced Company first before heading to the fifth floor. I wish you luck in your adventures.
She handed us our licenses.
We left the mostly empty building.
